translated: Blomstrand, Johan Harald, parish priest, Sävsjö, born January 22, 1905 in Madura, India, to former missionary Theodor B. and Hilda Carlson. Married Margit Berger in 1930. Children: Anders born 1932, Anita born 1934, Ingegerd born 1936, Magdalena born 1940 (deceased), Maj born 1942, and Gunnil born 1943. Blomstrand earned his high school diploma in Kalmar in 1923, his Bachelor of Theology degree in 1924, and completed his practical theology exam and was ordained as a priest for the Växjö diocese in 1927. He was posted to Döderhult and Resmo, was a curate in Vallsjö starting in 1930, and served as the parish priest there from 1940. He was appointed as the district dean in the Västra härads district in 1942. He was a speaker at the 1947 annual clergy meeting in Växjö, inspector of Sävsjö's public schools and vocational schools, and speaker for the Sävsjö Music Society.
